rComments: As a coordinator, Peterson is difficult - CSC108 is an introduction to programming class with many people who have prior experience. Yet the midterm mean was 60% and the exam mean was 53%. As a lecturer Peterson is great, he makes things clear and he knows what he is talking about. The only thing is it can be scary to talk to him about grades.

Andrew Peterson is one of the best professors/teachers I have ever had. He cares a lot about his students and gives amazing feedback. He has amazing stories and is really actively accessible. He is a little tough and others often use that to define him but he is a great professor and an awesome person as well. 10/10 would recommend

The format of the course was awful, the online assignments were graded roughly and midterm had a whole different format from the rest in the past few years. Also, in the midterm, one of the classes got 10 minutes less to finish their examinations!
Mediocre at best. CSC108? Really? He makes us fear Python.
Bad

PCRS was not the most helpful in teaching concepts, Lectures, were a lot of worksheets and him explaining on the board. Most learning came from labs which were thrown at you. Assignments were fair once you understood the idea behind it however required starting as soon as possible to finish on time. Exam and Test were fair, but hard due to time.

Andrew, ran the course differently this year. The only real good part was his lectures as they were extremely useful. But this year the main learning came from reading the textbook chapters assigned every week. THE TEXTBOOK SUCKS. Weekly quizs were fair but labs are impossible to finish in 2 hours starting beforehand was required.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: He doesnt actually teach in class. Youre better off skipping and reading the book at home.
Not bad
This mans job is to weed out first years. He only thinks in terms of POSt and wants to minimize your GPA as well as he can. Assignments were super difficult. Good luck.
Best Prof ever! He wants every student challenges themselves. Very accessible. You can basically sit in his office and chat with him the entire office hour as long as no one has a real question.

Decent prof but his assignments are extremely hard. Made one to for the purpose of kicking first years out of cs. Take 108 only if u have coded before and is basically an expert in it, if u have never coded before, don't take cs with him

Petersen is a good prof. He's kind of harsh tho, as in he'll say what he thinks, but I feel like he doesn't intend to be bad to anyone. He's strict, his marking scheme is just awful, but I think as a prof he's not bad. Take him with caution though, 209 last year was a pretty big mess.

You'll learn a lot in this course, but it will take a lot of work, and your marks won't necessarily reflect your effort. Tests are fair, but the assignments are HARD. Pay attention to detail, take advantage of remarks, and don't skip the weekly labs.

Andrew is not only one of the best teachers I've ever had but he also one of kindest people ever I've met . He's extremely knowledgeable and truly cares for students. Attend his office hours when you need help, or even just go to say hi, you'll love him, hes so easy to talk to and hes genuinely so kind to students and willing to help with anything.
He is the best prof I've ever had. He is really encouraging and knowledgeable. He is not an easy prof, but definitely take his courses, you will enjoy it for sure!
As I've heard someone else say - ''The pinnacle of a prof to fear'.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I took CSC108 without any CS background. I have to admit it was not an easy class, but I learned so much! He was really helpful and encouraging students to work harder and try their best. If you're taking 108, take it with this guy!!

He is knowledgable, and his course covers lots of materials. Take his course, you will know he really love teaching and willing to help students! His course is usually hard, but he like to spend time on solve your problems. As long as you want to learn, he will afford as many help as you need.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: He's really caring and wants to help everyone. If your stuck, immediately go visit him in his office hours or ask a question on the class discussion board (if you have one). Course isn't tricky if you actually listen in class and pick up on the things he emphasizes.  He's like super smart so don't be intimidated !!

This is the hardest course I've ever taken. The assignments are killer and you'll spend days in the lab, I even slept over once. Weekly quizzes and interviews for each assignment. Tough but worthwhile, you get a good understanding of how computer works. Probably not worth taking for a major (since you don't need it). GOOD LUCK IF YOU TAKE IT.
He'll challenge you, but is there to help the entire way. Incredibly pedantic.  If you're stuck, visit him during office hours.  He's probably the best prof I've had so far in CS.
Absolutely amazing prof, take anything he teaches. Very helpful and friendly, midterms and assignments are straightforward.
Good prof. Definitely take a course with him as an instructor!
hes a good prof :)
Crystal clear explications. Extremely approachable and truly willing to help.
Great Professor.
The best

Among all of my professors in first year, he stands out the most. Relates himself to his students, and that's where most professors fail to accomplish. I suggest you to enroll to any course he teaches. I wasn't interested when I took 108, but wow! I was impressed, so I took 148 as well. And I will see him at 207! Very nice overall.

Very clear explanations, fair and quick grading. Midterm/exam questions reflect on what was taught in class. Classes are never boring, although the material sometimes is. Extremely approachable and very nice!
excellent prof!
Best prof ever, extremely helpful, kind and understanding.

Best prof I've ever had! He's so helpful and also eager to answer students' questions during the lecture. Lecture is well organized and he  always give clear explanations about the materials. He also has a good manner and humour. :D

Not too easy on the marking but a great prof! Very clear in his explanations, lectures are organized and laid out very well, works through useful examples, very helpful especially in discussion board, provides great online notes and code.
Excellent prof, especially for anxious first years. Knows what he is talking about and keeps lectures interesting with his unique humour.
